properties.ai:description:
RV Franklin Voyage FR 10/87 -  The voyage took place in the Indian Ocean and the Gulf of Carpentaria during 3-24 November 1987. This record was created as the following paper documents located in box file "FR10/87 EB" received from Ed Butler were scanned and archived.The box file "FR 10/87 EB" can be found in the Datacentre store room, Building 5,  5SS54 -bay 3, shelf 4.

On-line Documentation: (added as of: 12/08/2014)
-fr198710_BridgeLog_Copy.pdf
-fr198710_EventLog_Computer.pdf
-fr198710_EventLog_Original.pdf
-fr198710_Cruise_Summary.pdf


Documentation is on the internal network: \processedVoyageData\RV_Franklin  [voyage]  \global_docs.

The raw data archive is part of an LTO backup tape which holds the entire raw data collection from all Franklin voyages. Date range 1985 - 2002. Data from all MAG tapes, /data tapes, echolog tapes and echolog CDs is included. See http://www.marine.csiro.au/marq/edd_search2.cd_details?id=519 for details.
properties.statement: Data source: original field data.  The following paper documents located in box file "FR10/87 EB" received from Ed Butler were scanned and added on: 12/08/2014: fr198710_BridgeLog_Copy.pdf, fr198710_EventLog_Computer.pdf, fr198710_EventLog_Original.pdf, fr198710_Cruise_Summary.pdf. The box file "FR 10/87 EB" can be found in the Datacentre store room, Building 5,  5SS54 -bay 3, shelf 4. Raw data for voyages prior to 2010 will be retrieved from LTO Tape and added to the local rawVoyageData network area. This raw data archive will be archived by the CSIRO Data Access Portal in 2015.
